# Theming

The Bolt Design System supports two themes: **light** and **dark**. The default template uses the **dark** theme.

## Switching Themes

Themes are controlled by a `data-theme` attribute on the root `<html>` element:

```html
<!-- Dark theme (default) -->
<html data-theme="dark">

<!-- Light theme -->
<html data-theme="light">
```

In React, update the attribute dynamically:

```tsx
// Switch to light theme
document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'light');

// Switch to dark theme
document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'dark');
```

Or set it in your HTML entry file:

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  ...
</html>
```

## UnoCSS Dark Mode Configuration

The design system uses UnoCSS for styling. The dark mode selector must be configured in `uno.config.ts`:

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'unocss';
import { unoThemeColors } from '@blitz/design-system/tokens/unocss/theme';

export default defineConfig({
  theme: {
    colors: unoThemeColors,
  },
  dark: {
    light: '[data-theme="light"]',
    dark: '[data-theme="dark"]',
  },
});
```

## CSS Token Variables

Tokens are defined in `theme.css` imported as:

```ts
import '@blitz/design-system/tokens/unocss/theme.css';
```

The CSS file uses `:root[data-theme='light']` and `:root[data-theme='dark']` selectors (with `:root` alone aliased to light):

```css
/* Light theme tokens (default) */
:root, :root[data-theme='light'] {
  --bolt-ds-brand: 43 166 255;
  --bolt-ds-surface: 254 254 255;
  --bolt-ds-textPrimary: 17 17 20;
  /* ... */
}

/* Dark theme tokens */
.dark, :root[data-theme='dark'] {
  --bolt-ds-brand: 20 136 252;
  --bolt-ds-surface: 17 17 20;
  --bolt-ds-textPrimary: 254 254 255;
  /* ... */
}
```

## Token Values Per Theme

### Brand Tokens

| Token | Light | Dark |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--bolt-ds-brand` | `rgb(43 166 255)` | `rgb(20 136 252)` |
| `--bolt-ds-brandHighlight` | `rgb(83 196 255)` | `rgb(43 166 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-onBrand` | `rgb(255 255 255)` | `rgb(238 249 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-brandContainer` | `#eef9ff` | `#2ba6ff1a` |
| `--bolt-ds-onBrandContainer` | `rgb(18 47 89)` | `rgb(43 166 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-brandOutline` | `#2ba6ff33` | `#2ba6ff1a` |

### Surface Tokens

| Token | Light | Dark |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--bolt-ds-surface` | `rgb(254 254 255)` | `rgb(17 17 20)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceAltLight` | `rgb(243 243 248)` | `rgb(30 30 33)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceAltDark` | `rgb(243 243 248)` | `rgb(17 17 20)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceOne` | `rgb(254 254 255)` | `rgb(30 30 33)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceTwo` | `rgb(233 233 240)` | `rgb(44 44 48)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceThree` | `rgb(212 212 221)` | `rgb(44 44 48)` |
| `--bolt-ds-surfaceHighlight` | `#0000000d` | `#ffffff14` |
| `--bolt-ds-inverseSurface` | `rgb(30 30 33)` | `rgb(254 254 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-inverseOnSurface` | `rgb(254 254 255)` | `rgb(30 30 33)` |

### Text & Icon Tokens

| Token | Light | Dark |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--bolt-ds-textPrimary` | `rgb(17 17 20)` | `rgb(254 254 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-textSecondary` | `#0a0a0abf` | `#ffffffbf` |
| `--bolt-ds-textTertiary` | `#0a0a0a99` | `#ffffff99` |
| `--bolt-ds-iconPrimary` | `rgb(17 17 20)` | `rgb(254 254 255)` |
| `--bolt-ds-iconSecondary` | `#0a0a0a80` | `#ffffff80` |

### Border Tokens

| Token | Light | Dark |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--bolt-ds-borderOutline` | `#0000001a` | `#ffffff1a` |
| `--bolt-ds-borderDivider` | `#00000026` | `#ffffff26` |

## Customizing Theme Colors

Override `--bolt-ds-*` CSS custom properties in your own stylesheet after importing `theme.css`:

```css
/* Custom brand color override */
:root[data-theme='dark'] {
  --bolt-ds-brand: 120 80 255;  /* purple brand instead of blue */
  --bolt-ds-brandHighlight: 150 110 255;
  --bolt-ds-onBrandContainer: 120 80 255;
}

:root[data-theme='light'] {
  --bolt-ds-brand: 100 60 240;
  --bolt-ds-brandHighlight: 130 90 255;
  --bolt-ds-onBrandContainer: 18 10 60;
}
```

Note: Many token values are stored as space-separated RGB triplets (without `rgb()` wrapper) to support UnoCSS opacity modifiers like `bg-bolt-ds-brand/50`.

## Using Tokens in UnoCSS

```tsx
// Background using brand color
<div className="bg-bolt-ds-brand">

// Text color
<p className="text-bolt-ds-textPrimary">

// With opacity
<div className="bg-bolt-ds-brand/20">

// Surface colors
<div className="bg-bolt-ds-surface">
<div className="bg-bolt-ds-surfaceOne">
```

## Default Template Configuration

The default template uses `data-theme="dark"`. To switch to light:

1. In `index.html`: change `data-theme="dark"` to `data-theme="light"`
2. That's it â€” all component tokens will automatically use their light-mode values.

