A utility function for conditionally joining CSS class names together. Accepts any combination of strings, booleans, undefined values, arrays, or objects where keys are class names and values are booleans determining inclusion.

Usage:
```ts
import { classNames } from '@blitz/design-system/utils/classNames';

// Strings
classNames('foo', 'bar'); // 'foo bar'

// Conditionals via objects
classNames({ 'is-active': isActive, 'is-disabled': isDisabled });

// Mixed usage
classNames('base-class', isActive && 'active', { 'bold': isBold });
```

Signature:
```ts
function classNames(...args: ClassNamesArg[]): string
type ClassNamesArg = undefined | boolean | string | Record<string, boolean | undefined> | ClassNamesArg[];
```

A cubic easing function for use in animations and transitions. Takes a normalized time value `t` (0 to 1) and returns an eased value. Can be used with Framer Motion or other animation libraries to produce smooth, natural-feeling motion.

Usage:
```ts
import { cubicEasingFn } from '@blitz/design-system/utils/easings';

// Use as a custom easing in Framer Motion
const eased = cubicEasingFn(0.5);
```

Signature:
```ts
const cubicEasingFn: (t: number) => number;
```

A constant CSS selector string targeting the root Toastify container element. Useful for programmatically querying or styling toast notification containers.

Usage:
```ts
import { TOAST_SELECTORS } from '@blitz/design-system/utils/toast-selectors';

const container = document.querySelector(TOAST_SELECTORS);
// TOAST_SELECTORS === '.Toastify'
```

Signature:
```ts
const TOAST_SELECTORS: ".Toastify";
```
